To add message to a syslog file:

http://aspiringsysadmin.com/blog/2007/07/13/better-scripts-3-use-logger/

1. create the target file

touch /export/home/steve/src/working/lib/core/syslogtest/files/mltest.log

2. modify /etc/syslog.conf

local0.notice                                   /export/home/steve/src/working/lib/core/syslogtest/files/mltest.log

3. Restart service

svcadm restart svc:/system/system-log:default

4. test by sending a message

logger -p local0.notice my first local0 message

5. Log file should contain

Mar 10 13:29:40 ml-solaris steve: [ID 702911 local0.notice] my first local0 message



